Wash and quarter potatoes. Place in a large pot filled with lightly salted water. Bring water to a boil and boil potatoes 15-20 minutes or until tender when pierced with a fork. Drain and set aside. Chop bacon into strips. Place oil in a large skillet. Heat over medium-high heat. Add bacon and cook until lightly browned. Add onion and cook approximately 5 more minutes or until onions are translucent. Blend SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener, flour and salt together in a small bowl. Stir into pan and cook briefly (approx. 1 min.). Add water and vinegar while stirring constantly. Add potatoes and stir well. Garnish with chopped parsley. Serve immediately.